. The edge and matrix adjacent to large fragments tend to have closely related lineages nonetheless, suggesting phylogenetic homogenization in these IEM gradient categories. Thus, despite the high mobility of bats, fragmentation still induces considerable levels of erosion of phylogenetic diversity, suggesting that the full amount of evolutionary history might not be able to persist in present-day human-modified landscapes.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Aninta, Sabhrina G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rocha, Ricardo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "L\u00f3pez-Baucells, Adri\u00e0", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Meyer, Christoph F. J.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/1f9431ff1ff44ddd13f2ee17ad1cd75e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/3ca76ab5f27d88d1c686642037ddfffb9876528ba459943db05483b1b702f39a", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/F5TSKZWD", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/F5TSKZWD", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/4fdf782a55c6a66e8dcdd8adf7aa5bb1!/b308441-310905", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "14", "pages": "4047-4063", "title": "Biodiversity and Conservation", "volume": "28"}, "alternate_iden